  "diary": "Woke up early to a gorgeous morning—the kind that makes you grateful to live in Seattle, even if only for a day. Espresso went down smooth before heading downtown to Pioneer Square for the site check. The crew was sharp, everything on schedule, which always puts me in a better mood.\n\nAround ten, I couldn't resist ducking into the Crocodile with a couple guys to catch the USA-Wales match. Grabbed a burger, had some laughs. We didn't win, but the energy in there was fun anyway. Back to work by noon, pushing through material inspections and permit stuff until mid-afternoon.\n\nHome by three. I've been getting into sourdough lately—there's something grounding about it. Prepped the starter, checked yesterday's dough. Made a simple pasta with homemade sauce and spent the evening knitting while listening to a podcast. Low-key, but exactly what I needed. Feeling settled.",
